name: backfill-native-banner-ad
hypothesis:
Native backfill will increase fill rate across banner inventory.
By supplementing standard banners with native ad content, we expect to serve more impressions that would otherwise go unfilled.


Native ad formats will maintain or improve user engagement metrics (e.g. retention, session length).
Seamless visual integration of native ads is less likely to disrupt user experience compared to low-quality or blank banners.


Time-to-load for native backfill will not materially degrade app performance.
Optimized rendering of native units will preserve app responsiveness and avoid introducing latency.

summarySections.name: Hypothesis
summarySections.content: By strategically implementing 'Profile Open' interstitial ads with segmented loads, delayed triggers, and market-specific targeting (outside Top 20 markets), we hypothesize that Grindr can achieve a significant increase in ad revenue without negatively impacting key user engagement metrics such as profile views per user, chat initiation rates, and session lengths. Furthermore, delaying the first interstitial ad to after 10 profile opens and providing a grace period for new users will mitigate initial user friction and contribute to a more positive user experience, thereby supporting long-term user retention and engagement.
